<DOC><DOCNO> AP891026-0245 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-26-89 1327EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Avon     10-26 0283</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Earns-Avon,0294</SECOND><HEAD>Avon Posts Quarterly Earnings After Loss Last Year</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Cosmetics company Avon Products Inc. on Thursdayreported a third-quarter profit of $34.6 million after losing moneya year earlier due to the cost of discontinuing some operations.   Avon earned 46 cents a share in the three months ended Sept. 30compared to a loss of $405.9 million, or $7.78 a share, in thethird 1988 quarter, when the company took a $425 million after-taxcharge for discontinued operations.   Worldwide sales grew 8 percent in the third quarter to $785.1million from $725.6 million a year earlier.   James E. Preston, Avon's chairman and chief executive officer,attributed the company's earnings growth to aggressive expensereduction programs.   The New York-based direct sales company implemented new costcontrols and speeded up the sales of certain holdings earlier thisyear when it was facing unwanted takeover interest.   Looked at geographically, Avon said its third-quarter directsales slipped a little in the United States, falling 2 percent,while international sales grew 14 percent. Strong sales in LatinAmerica are compensating for a below-plan performance in the UnitedKingdom and continental Europe, Avon said.   Avon's retail fragrance division, comprising Giorgio BeverlyHills and Parfums Stern, had a 41 percent increase in pre-taxprofit on a 35 percent sales gain. Avon has said that it isexploring the sale of its retail business.   For the first nine months of the year, Avon earned $80.3 milion,or 97 cents a share, compared with a loss of $461.1 million, or$7.20 a share, through the first three quarters of last year.   Nine-month sales came to $2.27 billion, up 11 percent from theprior year's $2.05 billion.</TEXT></DOC>